// Been hyped for this one!! What started out as a @TimothyGoodman-designed art basketball court in 2020 for schools in Brooklyn, led to a new KD 15 collab featuring Timothy’s signature artwork and designs.

Caught up with Timothy recently to get the full story on his latest collab with @EasyMoneySniper and his expressive Brooklyn-tribute design.

“I wanted to make something that I felt like was one of the dopest shoes that I’ve ever seen on the court and something that could live off of the court,” he said. “Or, you want to put it on a shelf as a piece of art.”

Swipe 👈🏼 to check out the original court design and the many details throughout the new KD 15 and let me know what you think of the newest KD collab below. You can check out the full Q&A on @Boardroom

// Happy #AirMaxDay, to all who celebrate ‼️

My annual confession is I’ve actually never been much of an Air Max fan — have 1 pair of AM 97s and always preferred Zoom Air. I did always love these Max Hyperflights from 2012 though.

I first remember stumbling upon an iridescent Hyperflight sample from 2001 around 2008. [Swipe 👈🏼] There was just one size 13 right shoe lying around the NSW office, that we convinced everyone to let us photograph for an issue of Sole Collector Magazine. They actually inspired a SC collab Hyperdunk 2010 sample the following year. 

That sample didn’t get close to the true color spectrum of that iridescent Hyperflight, so we scrapped the concept and went with the Anthracite / Vivid Blue / Neon colorway instead.

A few years later, the NSW team led by @MarcDolce turned that iridescent sample into a reality, bringing the colorful look to the modernized Max Hyperflight. 

What other sample concepts would you want to see re-imagined again?

// ‼️ AUCTION TIME ‼️

Been fortunate over the years to get access to more shoes than I coulda dreamed of as a kid — and it’s time to downsize the collection and sell off a ton of pairs on @WhatNot with @HesKicks.

The auction is TODAY May 25th at 7 PM EST and SUNDAY May 28th at 2 PM EST on @HesKicks’ page at WhatNot.com/user/HesKicks (or link in bio) Most are size 13/14 and there’s also samples in sz 9, random PEs and a few other sizes mixed in.

Excited to put this together and help raise money for the girls & boys’ basketball teams at my middle school, Sutter Middle in Sacramento !! 

Playing hoops on the Miners those 2 years was some of the best times ever. And fun fact: My 7th grade Shake Ndestrukts, that I got for $19.99 at Ross, once got sent to Nike’s factory in Asia as reference to help with the design and shape of the Max Shake Evolve & Shake Ndestrukt Retro. 🤯 Still have ‘em.

// Capped off May tracking down what I’m gonna call ‘The Chase Pack’ — 3 awesome shoes from the 2003 era that each represent the frenzy to sign LeBron James out of SVSM exactly twenty years ago.

I spent the first half of the year working with @AarDodson on one of the proudest pieces I’ve ever put together — chronicling the craziest athlete chase in sneaker industry history through new untold stories and perspectives from the key people involved. You can read it on ESPN’s Andscape or via the link in my bio.

There was a $100 Million dollar expectation off top. A Malibu mansion. A signature shoe designed for a high schooler that just turned 18. Private jets, prototypes, alternate logo options, 5-figure presentation books and pitch meetings. 

The theatrics and bidding war between Nike, Adidas & Reebok was insane — and I wouldn’t at all be surprised to see it come to life as an AIR 2 movie one day.

// This page means everything to me !!

My whole life growing up I was reading Scoop, Bobbito & Russ set the foundation for what it meant to write about sneakers and hoops.

Was honored when @SLAM reached out for their Top 100 Basketball Sneakers Issue this spring and asked for my Top 10 list, alongside that very trio of legends.

What’s your Top 10 list?? Was awesome to see how different everyone’s favorites ranked out, and the eras of hoop covered over the years.
